From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: cppmega.mlx <noreply@example.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 12:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] tilelang: fuse Metal fp8_scaled_matmul scheduler

Add a Metal scheduler for T.fp8_scaled_matmul that keeps FP8 storage compact,
decodes packed e4m3 bytes with the Metal LUT dot4 helper, and applies the
selected A/B scale inside the contracted-K loop. The M=1 specialization emits
one SIMD-group per output row and uses simd_sum, matching the hand-written
audiohacking-style MSL shape used by cppmega.mlx Path C.

The scheduler accepts the existing per-tensor/per-row scale contract and carries
the block-scale metadata added by the e8m0 follow-up:

  T.fp8_scaled_matmul(
      A_fp8, A_scale, B_fp8, B_scale, C,
      transpose_B=True,
      scale_format="e8m0_block_k32",
      scale_block_size=32,
  )

Scale multiplication is deliberately fused into the load/FMA path. The emitted
Metal must not materialize a post-loop "C *= scale" epilogue.

